narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: Evaluating fictions as more in-depth commentary.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: As a small seminar, it allowed for great discourse between Professor Berger and all students, the classes really felt more like informal discussion of material we had all enjoyed absorbing.
I thought the fictional readings were all very interesting, and some of the articles offered interesting ideas, but it might have been helpful to organize the course more thematically.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: If you are willing to read a book plus some background readings each week and are prepared to discuss them intensively in a small group, this is a great course for you.
